content: Love it need more stuff but I love it thank you

This app is very buggy and needs a great deal of refinement. + Navigation is awkward. + Interface lacks a polished aesthetic. + Library of plants is pretty patchy. With some glaring holes and oversimplified (there are hundreds of species of eucalypts not one). Description is pretty lacking with some. Not all include pictures. The pictures included aren't great for identifying the plants. Can't them view full screen. This app has a lot of potential but I feel like it really is in beta

hope creator takes this as constructive criticism. wonderful idea & would like to see improved. There is almost NO constructive information, variation of pictures, or locations found. Some plant information states that there is too much to write about said plant that would fill the page but only gives one information. Stating that makes a reader feel creator is not motivated to make the app properly. Please look at apps like Audubon for info placement. Purchased to see if buying book is worth it
a app to help live off the grid to daily food, wow

Great app! There is only one problem. I am limited to about 25 favorites. I would really like to be to add more to my favorites. I have been limited in my research cause of this. please fix that feature :) Wonderful research on these plants. It is amazing how many people give this indescribable look cause I eat flowers and common weeds with the help of this app. I would gladly recommend this too my friends and family.

Very disappointing. Poor navigation. Tiny writing & pics on thumbnails used to select individual plants. Duplication of items. Almost no information given to help identify plants, and no way of searching for a plant by feature. Information given is almost entirely of uses as folk medicine, and disclaimers for everything. The most disappointing app I have ever bought, poor function and woeful content. Removing it same day, only kept it this long to find something good to say (I failed).
Im grateful and love all of Markus R. work
Phenomenal, very user friendly and I refer to it often as it has all the complete information on all you need to know about plants, exceptional work Markus....thank you.
Yummy
Very good app, works like it's supposed to and is informative. When you favorite something and close out the app it disappears along with anything else you favorited. A fix would be appreciated.
Excellent to spot wild plants in my surroundings
Tell's all out door plants to live off.I lost it after att did master reset.reinstalled and it had to get sent back.So don't know if I still have it?
Don't like starting from beginning when hitting back botton. But like it overall.
You cannot zoom the small pictures so it's hard to know what he is talking about.
Bad interface, limited library
Ive found this app to be extremely helpful, with great depth and detail.  Definitely the best one I have found in this category. One suggestion adding woundwort (stachys salvation) excellent work.

Even on my tablet some of the photos are too small for proper identification. More identification details should also be given if you are planning to use this to identify a plant to eat. It does contain some good information.
Minimal information about different plants. Not easy to identify them. No info on where in US they can be found.

Astounding depth of information!  I tried every "edible plant guide" out there, this App blows them all away. It is SO fantastic to be able to save an indentified plant to my Favourites.  This enables me to prepare for a foraging mission.  I can review the information, get the excellent pictures in my mind, and spot what I want to harvest much better. At the same time, the search function is unparalleled.  By category, by name... I LOVE THIS APP!
I'm addicted to raw foods! Thanks to the app, it makes identifying edible plants so much simpler!
I enjoy the app, great source of useful information. Only complaint is that when I click on a picture to see it enlarged the app stops working.
Really good app the pics also in large to get a better view sort of. Needs more plants and a little bigger or clearer pics however the best I have found yet so I am happy TY

I like the app because it's always with me and gave lots of informations. But lots of pictures are doubled  (Example in section berries ~ 3x Squaw Brush). Pictures need higher resolution for better identification. Eggplant is under section non~edible but you can find that plant in lots of italian dishes. That confuse me.

Really love the app and all the details. Having one issue though. When I click on the picture of a plant to zoom in and get a closer look, I am not able to go back and have to restart the app to make it work again. Fix this issue and I'll give 5 stars.

This is a good app full of info but I would really like it if when I add to favorites it doesn't delete my favorites list when I exit off the app. Also it would be really helpful if you put down where certain plants are found around the world. Other then that it's a great app.
Do not listen the idiot said there is no description. Everything has full of description and good explanation.  I also have this book with me. Its very very good.
I love it thank you so much! Very simple looking
I have it as an ebook and hard cover and now app....i love it

This guide is so poorly developed it would be dangerous for the novice to try to use. Pictures only. No description or Id pointers. No range maps which for anyone remotely knowledgeable in plant id knows how important this single point is. Do not waste your time or money in this app. Find a dependable one. THIS IS NOT IT.
Would be 10 stars if plants could be sorted by region.
Has lots of health conditions and the plants to use for them.
Extremely informative and helpful
The book is  in app is a right move ...thank you for making it
Absolutely love the Diagnosis section of this app! Everything is so detailed and the pictures are crystal clear and easy to identify.
It doesn't get better than this to have this app on the go is priceless!
Thank you
It has great information about each plant its a great app for an everyday use I recommend this app for a healthy lifestyle
